===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|game|lang=enm}}, {{term|gamen|lang=enm}}, {{term|gammen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|gamen||sport, joy, mirth, pastime, game, amusement, pleasure|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|gamanan||amusement, pleasure, game", literally "participation, communion, people together|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{recons|ga-|pos=collective prefix|lang=gem-pro}} + {{recons|mann-||man|lang=gem-pro}}, equivalent to {{prefix|ge|man}}; or alternatively from {{recons|ga-|lang=gem-pro}} + a root from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|men-||to think, have in mind|lang=ine-pro}}, equivalent to {{prefix|ge|mind}}. Cognate with {{etyl|gmh|-}} {{term|gamen||joy, amusement, fun, pleasure|lang=gmh}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|gamman||mirth, rejoicing, merriment|lang=sv}}, {{etyl|is|-}} {{term|gaman||fun|lang=is}}. Related to {{l|en|gammon}}, {{l|en|gamble}}.

